        4298
      ],
      "content": "<ph id=\"ph1\">![</ph>Warning Icon<ph id=\"ph2\">](./media/storsimple-safety/IC740879.png)</ph> <ph id=\"ph3\">![</ph>Electrical Shock Icon<ph id=\"ph4\">](./media/storsimple-safety/IC740882.png)</ph> <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>WARNING!<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>"
    },
    {
      "content": "To reduce the likelihood of overheating or fire from the electrical connections:",
      "pos": [
        4300,
        4380
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Provide a suitable power source with electrical overload protection to meet the requirements detailed in the technical specification.",
      "pos": [
        4384,
        4517
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Do not use bifurcated power cords (“Y” leads).",
      "pos": [
        4521,
        4567
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "To comply with applicable safety, emission, and thermal requirements, no covers should be removed and all bays must be populated with plug-in modules or drive blanks.",
      "pos": [
        4571,
        4737
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Ensure that the equipment is used in a manner specified by the manufacturer.",
      "pos": [
        4741,
        4817
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "If this equipment is used in a manner not specified by the manufacturer, the protection provided by the equipment may be impaired.",
      "pos": [
        4818,
        4948
      ]
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        4950,
        5016
      ],
      "content": "<ph id=\"ph1\">![</ph>Notice Icon<ph id=\"ph2\">](./media/storsimple-safety/IC740881.png)</ph> <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>NOTICE:<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>"
    },
    {
      "content": "For the proper operation of your equipment and to prevent product damage:",
      "pos": [
        5018,
        5091
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The RJ45 ports at the back of the device are for an Ethernet connection only.",
      "pos": [
        5095,
        5172
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "These must not be connected to a telecommunications network.",
      "pos": [
        5173,
        5233
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Be sure to install the device in a rack that can accommodate a front-to-back cooling design.",
      "pos": [
        5237,
        5329
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "All plug-in modules and blank plates are part of the system enclosure.",
      "pos": [
        5333,
        5403
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "These must only be removed when a replacement can be immediately added.",
      "pos": [
        5404,
        5475
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The system must not be run without all modules or blanks in place.",
      "pos": [
        5476,
        5542
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Rack system precautions",
      "pos": [
        5547,
        5570
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The following safety requirements must be considered when you mount the device in a rack cabinet.",
      "pos": [
        5572,
        5669
      ]
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        5671,
        5798
      ],
      "content": "<ph id=\"ph1\">![</ph>Warning Icon<ph id=\"ph2\">](./media/storsimple-safety/IC740879.png)</ph> <ph id=\"ph3\">![</ph>Tip Hazard Icon<ph id=\"ph4\">](./media/storsimple-safety/IC740886.png)</ph> <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>WARNING!<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>"
    },
    {
      "content": "To reduce the likelihood of injury from a tip over:",
      "pos": [
        5801,
        5852
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The rack design should support the total weight of the installed enclosures and should incorporate stabilizing features suitable to prevent the rack from tipping or being pushed over during installation or normal use.",
      "pos": [
        5856,
        6073
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "When loading a rack, fill the rack from the bottom up and empty from the top down.",
      "pos": [
        6077,
        6159
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Do not slide more than one enclosure out of the rack at a time to avoid the danger of the rack toppling over.",
      "pos": [
        6163,
        6272
      ]
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        6274,
        6407
      ],
      "content": "<ph id=\"ph1\">![</ph>Warning Icon<ph id=\"ph2\">](./media/storsimple-safety/IC740879.png)</ph> <ph id=\"ph3\">![</ph>Electrical Shock Icon<ph id=\"ph4\">](./media/storsimple-safety/IC740882.png)</ph> <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>WARNING!<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>"
    },
    {
      "content": "To reduce the likelihood of injury, electrical shock, or death:",
      "pos": [
        6409,
        6472
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The rack should have a safe electrical distribution system.",
      "pos": [
        6476,
        6535
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "It must provide over-current protection for the enclosure and must not be overloaded by the total number of enclosures installed.",
      "pos": [
        6536,
        6665
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The electrical power consumption rating shown on the nameplate should be observed.",
      "pos": [
        6666,
        6748
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The electrical distribution system must provide a reliable ground for each enclosure in the rack.",
      "pos": [
        6752,
        6849
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The design of the electrical distribution system must take into consideration the total ground leakage current from all power supplies in all enclosures.",
      "pos": [
        6853,
        7006
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Note that each power supply in each enclosure has a ground leakage current of 1.0 mA maximum at 60 Hz, 264 volts.",
      "pos": [
        7007,
        7120
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The rack may require labeling with “HIGH LEAKAGE CURRENT.",
      "pos": [
        7121,
        7178
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Ground (earth) connection is essential before connecting a supply.”",
      "pos": [
        7179,
        7246
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The rack, when configured with the enclosures, must meet the safety requirements of UL 60950-1 and IEC 60950-1/EN 60950-1.",
