        7644,
        7808
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Power Cooling Module (PCM) precautions",
      "pos": [
        7813,
        7851
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The device is designed to operate with two PCMs.",
      "pos": [
        7853,
        7901
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Each of the PCMs has a power supply and a dual-axis fan.",
      "pos": [
        7902,
        7958
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "During a critical condition, the system allows for a failure of one power supply while continuing normal operations.",
      "pos": [
        7959,
        8075
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Two PCMs (and hence power supplies) must always be installed.",
      "pos": [
        8076,
        8137
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "A single PCM does not provide redundant power.",
      "pos": [
        8138,
        8184
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Therefore, the failure of even one PCM can result in downtime or possible data loss.",
